org.orgName: The District Court of the United States, Western District of Washington, Northern Division

div1.p: Whereas in cause No. 5943, being the petition of Yaichiro Goto for a writ of habeas corpus, the said petitioner has deposited by order of the Honorable Jeremiah Neterer the sum of $50.00 to cover his expense from the 1st day of April, 1921, and whereas said expense is approximately the sum of $15.00, and whereas E.P. Donnelly has this day paid to Yaichiro Goto the full balance of said deposit, or $35.00, and whereas it was necessary for said E. P. Donnelly to do this as the alien is about to be deported and he would otherwise have no opportunity of withdrawing said amount from the registry of the court. NOW THEREFORE:

Said Yaichiro Goto hereby sets over and assigns to E. P. Donnelly all his right title and interest in and to the money deposited by him in the above mentioned cause, subject to a charge of $15.12 incurred by him for board.
In the Court of the United States for the District of Washington
Filed in the United States District Court
Service of within and receipt of copy admitted this day of 191

We hereby designate Room No. Building Street , Washington as the place where all subsequent papers herein, except writs and process, may be made upon the herein, and consent that service of all subsequent papers herein, except writs and process, may be made as the place hereinabove designated upon the said
